In versions before ''[[Pixel Remaster]]'', Pyrolisk has 124 [[morale (Final Fantasy)|morale]], and only gains a chance to run away if the lead party member is Lv23 or higher.

== Battle ==
Pyrolisks appear in groups, and sometimes run away.

The Pyrolisk's physical attacks are slightly stronger than their cousin the [[Cockatrice (Final Fantasy)|Cockatrice]]'s, although they do not cause [[Stone (Final Fantasy status)|petrification]]. This does not mean Pyrolisks are unable to petrify the unwary; rather, the Pyrolisk uses its [[Gaze (ability)|Gaze]] skill to kill its enemies instantly, which the [[Gold Needle (Final Fantasy)|Gold Needle]] it [[Item drop|drops]] will most-assuredly not cure.

Despite being based on a creature that causes spontaneous combustion with its gaze, its Squint instant death ability is Death-elemental and not Fire-elemental, so only [[NulDeath (Final Fantasy)|NulDeath]] and gear with Death resistance will block its special ability.

Pyrolisks, being creatures of [[Fire (Final Fantasy element)|Fire]], are resistant to Fire-based magic but suffer a weakness from [[Ice (Final Fantasy element)|Ice]]-based magic. Even without Ice magic, they are not strong creatures and can be killed easily with strong physical attacks.

